  "texts": [
    "For example, Braines et al. (2019) propose a system where users can question and follow up on an explanation.",
    "Furthermore, both Sklar and Azhar (2018) and Hernandez-Bocanegra and Ziegler (2023) advocate for argumentation-based dialogues, fostering dynamic exchanges where users can question the system's suggestions.",
    "Inspired by the protocol of Madumal et al. (2019), Malandri et al. (2023) incorporate the possibility of clarification dialogues into Category Properties Supported dialogue types Examination dialogues (Walton 2016) Argumentation on explanations (Walton 2016; Madumal et al. 2019) Questioning explainee's request (Madumal et al.",
    "2019) Ability to adapt to the user Unique preceding dialogue phases (Shaheen et al. 2020) Differentiation in abstraction levels (Shaheen et al.",
    "2020) Explicitness of Goal Dialogue goal specification (Walton 2016; Shaheen et al. 2020) Criteria for goal achievement (Walton 2016)"
  ]
}